# Egonex-AI / Understand-Anything ignore file (starter)
#
# This file tells `/understand` what to skip during code analysis. It uses
# .gitignore-style globs. By default, every line below is COMMENTED OUT — the
# plugin generated it as a *starter* based on your project's detected languages
# (Astro, TypeScript/TSX, MDX, JSON, YAML). Review each section, uncomment the
# patterns you actually want excluded, and re-run `/understand` for the change
# to take effect.
#
# Note: this is independent from `.gitignore`. If a path is already excluded
# from your repo (e.g. node_modules, dist, .astro), `/understand` will skip
# it regardless of what's here. Use THIS file for analysis-specific exclusions.
#
# Reference: plugin SKILL.md Phase 0.5

# ----- Astro -----
# Tests & stories for Astro components
# **/*.test.astro
# **/*.spec.astro
# **/*.stories.astro

# ----- TypeScript / TSX -----
# Unit tests (Vitest, Jest, etc.)
# **/*.test.ts
# **/*.test.tsx
# **/*.spec.ts
# **/*.spec.tsx
# **/__tests__/**

# ----- End-to-end / Playwright -----
# e2e/**
# playwright/**
# playwright-report/**
# test-results/**

# ----- TinaCMS / Content (auto-generated) -----
# tina/__generated__/**

# ----- Build outputs -----
# .astro/**
# dist/**
# .vercel/**
# .next/**

# ----- Tooling / agent output -----
# .playwright-mcp/**
# .impeccable/**
# .prototools/**

# ----- Env & secrets -----
# .env
# .env.local
# .env.*.local

# ----- Dependencies -----
# node_modules/**

# ----- Lockfiles (optional — include them if you want them analyzed) -----
# **/pnpm-lock.yaml
# **/package-lock.json
# **/yarn.lock
